\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Chapter 12: The Festival}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The school festival was in full swing, the air filled with laughter and the smell of food. Haruhi stood backstage, watching as Nagano tuned his guitar. He looked nervous, his fingers trembling slightly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92ve got this,\u8221\'94 she said, giving him an encouraging smile.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 He nodded, taking a deep breath. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thanks. For everything.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 On stage, the emcee announced Nagano\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s performance. The crowd cheered as he walked out, his guitar slung over his shoulder. Haruhi spotted Honoka in the audience, her eyes fixed on Nagano.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The first notes of the song rang out, soft and haunting. Then Nagano began to sing, his voice filled with emotion. The lyrics Honoka had written told a story of dreams, longing, and the courage to reach for the stars.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As the song ended, the crowd erupted into applause. Nagano looked out at the audience, his eyes finding Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s. For a moment, it was just the two of them, connected by the music and the words they had created together.}
